Remote or Onsite - message if interested (therealpamplemoose at gmail dot com)<p>We are a venture-backed SaaS cybersecurity company (stealth) solving the largest and most complex problem in cybersecurity: social engineering.<p>Social engineering is not about technology infrastructure. It is about people sharing information with other people, and a vast body of valuable information at the fingertips of attackers who know how to make use of it.<p>That is why this is the largest cyber problem facing society today.
Role Description: Vice President of Engineering (member of leadership team)<p>As a key member of the leadership team, the VP of Engineering is responsible for the technical delivery of our solution to sophisticated enterprise cybersecurity customers.<p>In this role, you will be responsible for: --Managing the engineering organization from front-end UI to the collection and analysis of unstructured data;<p>+Aligning the technical roadmap against the product roadmap and business needs to deliver capability-rich SaaS solutions on time;<p>+Establishing, monitoring, and communicating KPIs to the rest of the executive team and Board of Directors; Improving engineering efficiency over time -- both in terms of technical efficiency and team dynamics;<p>+Increasing the technical value of the company over time through strong management and by crossing new technical ground;<p>Qualifications
We believe successful candidates will likely have some or all of following:<p>+Demonstrated success leading distributed teams of software engineers and data scientists who build cutting edge SaaS solutions as a VP of Engineering or similar role (CTO, Senior Director, or Director of Engineering);<p>+Both the social and technical ability to grow an existing engineering organization through coaching, hiring, and recruiting to support the proper team growth and technical architecture;<p>+Managerial and organizational skills for a coordinated large team over time;

C++ @ Summitto Amsterdam, Netherlands | Full-time | Onsite<p>We are building the largest invoice registration network of the world. The purpose? Helping EU tax authorities to eliminate 50 billion EUR in annual invoicing fraud. If you’re excited to build and design open-source software which will be used by millions of companies, we are looking for you! We&#x27;re hiring a senior developer at the moment. Experience with cryptography is a plus, but not required!<p>Here’s a little taste of your challenge, you will help:<p>* design large data analysis pipelines and tooling; 
* build cryptographic libraries and our core reporting system; 
* write APIs and surrounding documentation; 
* improve the efficiency and maintainability of our code and compilation tools;<p>Technologies: C++(11, 14, 17), JavaScript, Golang, Ansible.<p>Contact: <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;summitto.com&#x2F;careers.html" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;summitto.com&#x2F;careers.html</a>
